  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Cohesion and Sustainable Community Development in Conflict-Affected Communities in the Donbas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the present action is to contribute towards the Government of Ukraine&#x2019;s efforts to support socio-economic recovery through the promotion of inclusive, cohesive and stabilized communities affected by conflict in the Donbas region (GCA). IOM&#x2019;s social cohesion programming envisages the selection of conflict-affected communities hosting a large number of Internal Displaced Populations (IDPs), returnees, former participants of military action, with limited public and administrative services and existing social tensions. As a part of a holistic approach, the present action will be a part of a larger portfolio of activities aimed at building social cohesion through: empowerment of the local communities to hold inclusive events and activities that promote understanding between the host communities, minorities, IDPs and other socially vulnerable groups; support increased communication for host community members and IDPs to jointly address common challenges; and promotion of tolerance for cultural, racial and ethnic diversity in Ukraine to mitigate possible tensions; and provision of additional opportunities for women and promotion of equal opportunities for people with disabilities to strengthen the principles of inclusion.</narrative>
  </description>
